<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1238,1589]" pageId="8" pageNumber="493">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,436,1238,1264]" pageId="8" pageNumber="493">Description of male</emphasis>
[based on 
<typeStatus box="[561,660,1239,1265]" pageId="8" pageNumber="493">paratype</typeStatus>
, 
<quantity box="[673,760,1238,1265]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="8" pageNumber="493" unit="mm" value="3.5">3.5 mm</quantity>
(OMNH-Ar-12231)]. 
<emphasis box="[1014,1067,1239,1264]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="493">Eyes</emphasis>
larger than those of female. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="493">Antenna 1</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[253,320,1274,1301]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[197,1383,196,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-15@7.[183,1403,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 5. Metodius cyanomaculatus gen. et sp. nov. All but M: holotype, ovigerous female, 5.0 mm (OMNH-Ar-12230); M: paratype, male, 3.5 mm (OMNH-Ar-12231). Scales: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5683389/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="493">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
M-A1), primary flagellum stouter than that of female, with 8 articles, each bearing numerous aesthetascs. 
<emphasis box="[256,405,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="493">Gnathopod 2</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[422,488,1310,1337]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[197,1383,196,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-15@7.[183,1403,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 5. Metodius cyanomaculatus gen. et sp. nov. All but M: holotype, ovigerous female, 5.0 mm (OMNH-Ar-12230); M: paratype, male, 3.5 mm (OMNH-Ar-12231). Scales: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5683389/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="493">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
M-G2) subequal to that of female except for oostegite, but propodus more slender. 
<emphasis box="[151,280,1346,1373]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="493">Pereopod 7</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[296,362,1346,1373]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[197,1383,196,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-15@7.[183,1403,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 5. Metodius cyanomaculatus gen. et sp. nov. All but M: holotype, ovigerous female, 5.0 mm (OMNH-Ar-12230); M: paratype, male, 3.5 mm (OMNH-Ar-12231). Scales: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5683389/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="493">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
M-P7), coxa anterior margin with 8 plumose setae; basis more slender than that of female, with 7 anterior, 5 anterolateral and 2 anterodistal robust setae, inner surface lacking plumose setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1238,1589]" pageId="8" pageNumber="493">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,403,1418,1444]" pageId="8" pageNumber="493">Coloration in life</emphasis>
[based on 
<typeStatus box="[527,626,1419,1445]" pageId="8" pageNumber="493">paratype</typeStatus>
, male, 
<quantity box="[707,793,1418,1445]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="8" pageNumber="493" unit="mm" value="2.8">2.8 mm</quantity>
(OMNH-Ar-12232); 
<figureCitation box="[1037,1105,1418,1445]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1132,1156]" captionTargetBox="[176,1412,181,1108]" captionTargetId="figure-25@8.[176,1412,181,1108]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Metodius cyanomaculatus gen. et sp. nov. In situ photograph of paratype, male, 2.8 mm (OMNH-Ar-12232) taken on Nodahama Beach, Izu-ōshima Island (type locality, 10 m depth) on 23 December 2015 by O. Hoshino." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683391" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5683391/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="493">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
]. 
<emphasis box="[1127,1188,1418,1444]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="493">Head</emphasis>
white, eyes red. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="493">Body and coxae</emphasis>
brown, with ca. 15 bright blue spots and several white spots, dorsal margin of body framed in red. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="493">Antennae</emphasis>
white and partly bright red. 
<emphasis box="[511,679,1490,1517]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="493">Pereopods 5–7</emphasis>
except coxae white.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
